15/12/2003
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- EU security chief Javier Solana arrives in Belgrade on Monday (15 December) to discuss three key issues with Serbian authorities: improving the situation in Kosovo by meeting specific standards, the 28 December general elections in Serbia, and the functioning of the federation between Serbia and Montenegro. 
Solana is to meet with top Serbian and federal government officials.
In other news, the Council of Europe's consultative body on constitutional issues -- the Venice Commission -- has offered to help Montenegro in drafting constitutional changes. 
Podgorica has already set up an independent expert team to revise the constitution. 
(Tanjug, BBC, Vijesti - 14/12/03)
